TY  - JOUR
AU  - Bauer, Rob
AU  - Ruof, Tobias
AU  - Smeets, Paul
T1  - Get Real! Individuals Prefer More Sustainable Investments
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/08/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab037
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 8
SP  - 3976
EP  - 4043
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The United Nations’ Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) have created societal and political pressure for pension funds to address sustainable investing. We run two field surveys (n = 1,669, n = 3,186) with a pension fund that grants its members a real vote on its sustainable-investment policy. Two-thirds of participants are willing to expand the fund’s engagement with companies based on selected SDGs, even when they expect engagement to hurt financial performance. Support remains strong after the fund implements the choice. A key reason is participants’ strong social preferences.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab037
ER  - 



