TY  - JOUR
AU  - Eichholtz, Piet
AU  - Korevaar, Matthijs
AU  - Lindenthal, Thies
AU  - Tallec, Ronan
T1  - The Total Return and Risk to Residential Real Estate
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/08/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhab042
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 8
SP  - 3608
EP  - 3646
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We estimate total returns to rental housing by studying over 170,000 hand-collected archival observations of prices and rents for individual houses in Paris (1809–1943) and Amsterdam (1900–1979). The annualized real total return, net of costs and taxes, is 4.0% for Paris and 4.8% for Amsterdam and entirely comes from rental yields. Our returns weakly correlate with the implied returns in Jordà et al. (2019) and are substantially lower. We decompose total return risk at the individual asset level and find that yield risk becomes an increasingly important component of property-level risk for longer investment horizons.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhab042
ER  - 



